data.text:
Associated Press

Quotes from social media following the Cleveland Cavaliers’ victory in the NBA Finals:

———

“What a game and what a series for the @Cavs. Happy to see @KingJames bring it home for Cleveland!”

— President Barack Obama

———

“A wonderful demonstration of greatness! The @CityofCleveland, the @cavs organization, the team, the fans, and the great @KingJames..!”

— Cleveland Browns legend Jim Brown

———

“CHAMPIONS!!!! From CLEVELAND!!! #CAVS Thank you thank you thank you!!!!!”

— “The Price is Right” host and Cleveland native Drew Carey

———

“Salute to my brother @KingJames .. 3x Champion!!!”

— Dwayne Wade, LeBron James’ former Miami Heat teammate

———

“Wow. One of the best finals ever. So proud of King James. Salute Warriors Happy Father’s Day to all.”

— Rapper Jay Z

———

“unbelievable series to watch, congrats to cleveland. very well deserved. lebron and kyrie were next level good.”

— L.A. Clippers star Blake Griffin

———

“Lebron did it. Everybody be quiet. Goodnight.”

— Actor and singer Justin Timberlake

———

“Amazing series for a fantastic season. Love this game!! LBJ MVP without doubt, but Kyrie had some ridiculous moments.”

— Spurs guard Manu Ginobli

———

“SO happy and proud of my big Lil bro @KingJames and my Lil Lil bro @KyrieIrving & the rest of the CAVS... Way to go!!!! #proudfriend”

— Actress Gabrielle Union

———

“Congrats to the #CAVS and #CAVSNATION the was a great comeback, history was made tonight!!!!”

— Former Cavaliers forward Shawn Marion

———

“We just witnessed history....We will be talking about this game for years to come!!!!! Holy cow...”

— Actor and comedian Kevin Hart

———

“Congrats @cavs for winning @NBA title. @warriors u had a great regular season. But the greatest team of all time is the 95-96 @chicagobulls”

— Dennis Rodman, basketball hall of famer.

———

“watch me go off off off!!!!!! Kongrats to da King and da BOYZ!!!!”

— Rapper Lil Wayne

———

“Congratulation to BRON BRON and the cleveland Cavaliers , the city has been waiting long long time (hash)KingJames”

— Retired NBA legend Shaquille O’Neal

———

“I’m so happy for the good people of Cleveland! I’m so happy it wasn’t the Browns!”

— “Late Night” host Seth Meyers

———

“Unless you are from Cleveland, Ohio, you truly don’t understand how much this win means for the city.”

— Bills quarterback Cardale Jones, a Cleveland native who starred at Ohio State
